ating\nphoto-ionization, and are often well-aligned with lower metal ion species. PZFs\nare highly likely to affect the physical interpretation of circumgalactic high\nionization metal lines if, as expected, normal galaxies host flickering AGN.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 May 2017 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Apr 2018 23:05:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-13"}
